edu.ucla.sspace.util

Class SetDecorator<T>

  • java.lang.Object
    • edu.ucla.sspace.util.SetDecorator<T>
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    Serializable, Iterable<T>, Collection<T>, Set<T>

    public class SetDecorator<T>
extends Object
implements Set<T>, Serializable
    A wrapper around an existing Set implementation that allows subclasses to modify or extend the functionality of am existing Set instance by overriding some of its methods. For example, a subclass could enforce a size capacity on an existing set by overriding add and addAll to not add elements beyond a certain number.

    Instances of this class support all the optional operations supported by their contained set. All methods calls are passed through to the original set.

    Subclasses must override methods of this class to change existing functionality.
